.TH mip6d 1 "May 16, 2005" "" "Mobile IPv6, Proxy MIPv6 and NEMO Daemon"
.SH NAME
mip6d \- UMIP Mobile IPv6, Proxy MIPv6 and NEMO Basic Support protocol implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mip6d [options]
.sp
.SH DESCRIPTION

Mobile IPv6, Proxy MIPv6 and NEMO Basic Support implementation

.SH OPTIONS
.IP "\fB\-V, \-\-version\fP"
Display version information and copyright
.IP "\fB\-?, \-h, \-\-help\fP"
Display this help text
.IP "\fB\-c <file>\fP"
Read configuration from <file>.  If option is not present, default
path (%etc%/mip6d.conf) is used.
 
.PP
These options override values read from config file:
.IP "\fB\-d <number>\fP"
Set debug level (0-10)
.IP "\fB\-C, \-\-correspondent-node\fP"
Node is CN
.IP "\fB\-H, \-\-home-agent\fP"
Node is HA
.IP "\fB\-M, \-\-mobile-node\fP"
Node is MN

.SH SIGNALS

The following signals can be sent to the daemon:
.IP "\fB\ SIGHUP\fP"
Reload the configuration. See
.BR mip6d.conf (5)
for information on supported option reload.
.IP "\fB\ SIGINT, SIGTERM\fP"
Terminates the daemon operation.

.SH FILES

%etc%/mip6d.conf

